        All the big hits that went on ACR this week & my thoughts on them:

        ‘Snap’ – Gutted about this one, but hey, the fact that a Eurovision entry that finished 20th/26 went on to become very nearly a Top 20 hit a few months on from that, not to mention how well it did on streaming worldwide, is incredible nonetheless.

        ‘Sunroof’ – Sorry, but good riddance to this! I get why some people find it fun, but the vocals are so annoying.

        ‘Doja’ – Goofy, but ehh, didn’t really come back to it a lot! I don’t hate it, but I’m not upset to see it go either.

        ‘B.O.T.A.’ – Still doing well even for an ACR drop! As it should, it’s even starting to grow on me again.

        ‘Ferrari’ – Yeah, it’s had its time! Glad it crossed over from Europe, but the overplay made it cool off on me a little.

        ‘Not Over Yet’ – Disappointed, incredible song, but Tom Grennan getting another Top 40 hit softens the blow for me.

        ‘Ku Lo Sa’ – I really wanted to like this, Afrobeats is one of my favourite world genres, but there’s something about this that just didn’t work for me.

        ‘History’ – Ooh, I can think of a few regulars here who won’t be sorry to see this one go! As for me, I still don’t mind it & I’m kind of surprised how little it stuck around for, although both Joel & Becky have absolutely had better hits to their names.

        In the words of Olivia… god, it’s brutal out here! 😅
